# Walkthrough: Email Scrape, Gemini Extract, User Confirm & Phishing Analysis

We have connected the frontend browser extension with the python backend, utilizing Google's Gemini API for content extraction and structured formatting. We introduced a confirmation step allowing users to modify content before final evaluation and added a comprehensive cybersecurity diagnostics interface.

## Changes Completed

### 1. Graceful Gemini Integration & Extraction
- **File:** [gemini_extractor.py](file:///c:/Users/Ajinkya%20Patil/OneDrive/Desktop/Internship/Phishing%20Detection%20Assistant/backend/gemini_extractor.py)
  - Upgraded model configuration to `gemini-1.5-flash` for high efficiency, speed, and strict JSON extraction structure.
  - Handled missing `GEMINI_API_KEY` gracefully at runtime, falling back to local heuristic regex parsers instead of crashing on server startup.
- **File:** [app.py](file:///c:/Users/Ajinkya%20Patil/OneDrive/Desktop/Internship/Phishing%20Detection%20Assistant/backend/app.py)
  - Created a new `/extract-fields` POST route. This accepts scraped HTML content, routes it to the Gemini extractor, and yields cleaned JSON fields: `subject`, `sender`, and `body`.

