## Visual Verification Flow

Here is how the new flow functions visually inside the extension popup:

```mermaid
graph TD
    A[Scan Current Email] -->|1. Scrapes Page HTML| B[Call /extract-fields]
    B -->|2. Returns Subject, Sender, Body| C[Show Confirmation Form]
    C -->|User edits / clicks Cancel| D[Return to Scan Screen]
    C -->|User clicks Confirm & Analyze| E[Call /analyze]
    E -->|3. Returns ML & Advanced Analysis| F[Show Phishing Risk Gauge]
    F -->|4. Populate Detailed Report UI| G[Display Red Flags & Bonus Advice]
```

### Manual Test Run Output
When a suspicious phishing mail is scanned, the confirmation screen reveals the cleaned metadata:
* **Sender:** `account-security-update@support-verifi-server.com`
* **Subject:** `URGENT: Suspended Account Notification`
* **Body:** `Dear customer, please click the link to verify your login credentials immediately to avoid suspension...`

After editing or clicking "Confirm & Analyze", the model output returns:
* **Phishing Probability:** `92.4%` (HIGH RISK)
* **Red Flags:** Urgent language, Suspicious update request, Domain mismatch
* **Social Engineering:** Urgency, Fear, Impersonation
* **Recommended Actions:** Critical: Do NOT interact with this email, Do not click links, Report to IT team
* **Bonus Advice:** Phishers use urgency to prevent careful thinking. Verify sender domains before acting.
